{{otherships|HMS Jackal}}
'''HMS ''Jackal''''' was an [[Acheron class destroyer|''Acheron''-class destroyer]] of the [[Royal Navy]] that served during [[World War I]] and was sold for breaking in 1920.  She was the seventh [[Royal Navy]] ship to be named ''Jackal'', after the [[jackal|predatory mammal of the same name]].

==Construction==
She was built under the 1910-11 shipbuilding programme by [[R. W. Hawthorn Leslie & Company]] of [[Hebburn]], Tyneside<ref name=CAWFS>{{cite book |title=Conway's All the World's Fighting Ships 1906-1921 |year=1985 |publisher=Conway's Maritime Press |location=London |isbn=0-85177-245-5 |page=75}}</ref> to an Admiralty design and was launched on 9 September 1911.<ref name=BC>{{cite web|url=http://www.battleships-cruisers.co.uk/acheron.htm |title=Battleships-Cruisers.co.uk website - Acheron Class|accessdate=2008-06-30}}</ref> 

